        .col-xs-6.ui-article
          %h2 How to build a form
          .panel.panel-default.perforation
            .panel-heading
            .panel-body
              .form-group
                %p A basic form starts with a <em>.panel-default</em>, containing a <em>.panel-heading</em> and a <em>.panel-body</em>. Within the .panel-body, place a <em>.form-group</em>.
                %p The  Panel Heading can be left empty like this, thereby giving it a darker line to hang from.
                %p Here are some basic form elements:
                %label This is a label
                
                %input.form-control{value: 'This is an Form Control (%input.form-control)'}
                %p.help-block This is a <em>.help-block</em> paragraph
            .panel-perforation
          .panel.panel-default.perforated
            .panel-heading
              %h3 Your details
            .panel-body
              %h4 Address
              %p This is a form-horizontal, it places the lables to the left of the Input fields.
              .form-horizontal
                .form-group
                  %label.col-xs-4.control-label House Number
                  .col-xs-8
                    %input.form-control{value: ''}
                .form-group
                  %label.col-xs-4.control-label Street
                  .col-xs-8
                    %input.form-control{value: ''}
                .form-group
                  %label.col-xs-4.control-label Town/City
                  .col-xs-8
                    %input.form-control{value: ''}
                .form-group
                  %label.col-xs-4.control-label Postcode
                  .col-xs-8
                    %input.form-control{value: ''}
            .panel-perforation
          .panel.panel-default.perforated
            .panel-body
              .form-group
              %h4 Date of birth <em>%h4</em>
              %input.form-control{value: '', type: 'date'}
            .panel-perforation
        
          .panel.panel-default.perforated
            .panel-body
              %h4 Checkboxes and Radio buttons
              .form-group
                .checkbox
                  %label
                    %input{:type => "checkbox", :value => ""}/
                    Option one checkbox
                .checkbox.disabled
                  %label
                    %input{:disabled => "disabled", :type => "checkbox", :value => ""}/
                    Option two is a disabled checkbox
                .radio
                  %label
                    %input#optionsRadios1{:checked => "checked", :name => "optionsRadios", :type => "radio", :value => "option1"}/
                    Option one is a radio button, which will toggle with the one below.
                .radio
